	)
	(text "* For connection with\n  a host (embedded\n  SoC/MCU, PC, etc.).\n* Only USER Bus exposed\n  (SCL_TX/SDA_RX), can\n  be either I2C or UART.\n  Internal Peripheral\n  bus only accessible\n  from the HAT Headers.\n* D+ and D- is bypassed\n  to the host, but no\n  MUX controls it. Host\n  must communicate with\n  the board to know when\n  it's safe to use.\n* ~{RST} and BOOT are\n  useful for programming\n  the host, especially\n  if they're ST MCUs.\n\n\n\n* Pins:\n  - SCL_TX: SCL (I2C) / TX (UART)\n  - SDA_RX: SDA (I2C) / RX (UART)\n  - ~{IRQB}: Smart interrupt bus\n  - VCC: Supply, 5V or 3.3V, 1A max\n    on connectors, 3A on pin headers\n  - ~{BTN}: User side-button\n  - ~{RST}: Physical RESET signal\n  - D+: USB's D+ data line\n  - D-: USB's D- data line\n  - BOOT: Physical BOOT signal\n  - 5V, 3V3, VBUS, VOTG, VDD1: \n    Supply lines, 1A max on\n    connectors, 3A on pin headers\n\n* WARNING: Both VOTG and VBUS can be\n  up to 24V, depending on USB-PD\n  negotiation or external voltage\n  presented on VEXT! All other supply\n  lines are 5V max."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 133.35 66.04 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "a5e7db6c-3499-48f9-b8aa-93dd04c53628")
	)
	(text "VBUS"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 100.33 95.25 0)
		(effects
